Package: montyhall
Title: Simulate and Analyze the Monty Hall Problem
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    c(person("John", "Spaeth", , "jjspaeth@asu.edu", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Jesse", "Lecy", , "jlecy@asu.edu", role = c("aut")))
Description: The montyhall package provides a set of functions to simulate and analyze the famous Monty Hall Problem, a probability puzzle. It allows users to replicate the game's scenarios, including initial door selection, host's actions, and outcomes, facilitating experiments and research in probability theory and decision-making. Explore the nuances of the Monty Hall Problem and test different strategies to improve your understanding of probability.
